import imblearn
import pandas as pd

seed = 123
train = inputs[0]
col_names = train.columns
y_train = train.Y

def imbcode(x, thresh) :
    if x < thresh : 
        return 0
    else :
        return 1

code = y_train.apply(lambda x : imbcode(x, ${=threshold}))

which_os = ${=OverSampling}
if(which_os == 0):
  over_sample = imblearn.over_sampling.RandomOverSampler(sampling_strategy='minority', random_state=seed)
elif(which_os == 1):
  over_sample = imblearn.over_sampling.SMOTE(sampling_strategy='minority', random_state=seed, k_neighbors=5, n_jobs=1)
elif(which_os == 2):
  over_sample = imblearn.combine.SMOTEENN(sampling_strategy='minority', random_state=seed)

train_resample, code_resample = over_sample.fit_resample(train, code)

train_resample = pd.DataFrame(train_resample, columns = col_names)
code_resample = pd.DataFrame(code_resample, columns = ['CODE'])

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd

inputDataframe = inputs[0]


errro_abs=np.abs(inputDataframe["Answer"]-inputDataframe["Input"])
y_abs = np.abs(inputDataframe["Answer"])

sum_real_y=sum(y_abs)
wmae_val = 0

for i in range(0,300):
	wmae_val += y_abs[i]/sum_real_y*errro_abs[i]
	
#WMAE=sum((y_abs[i]/sum_real_y*errro_abs[i]) for i in range(0,300))

result_frame=pd.DataFrame([wmae_val])
result_frame.columns=["WMAE"]

res1=pd.DataFrame(errro_abs)
res1.columns=["errro_abs"]

res2=pd.DataFrame(y_abs)
res2.columns=["y_abs"]
